               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0198QS">Qalāqǝl Māryām Ṣǝyon</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1800">Second half of the 18th
                        cent.(?)
 The replacement of the name of the original donor with that of
                        Za-Manfas Qǝddus/daǧǧāzmāč Subagadis (1770-1831) hints that the Ms. was
                        written at least in the late 18th cent.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>The name of the original donor is Laʿǝkä
                     Māryām, mentioned in supplication formulas throughout the Ms. and in Additio 1.
                     His wife Fǝśśǝḥa Māryām (e.g., 16vc, 36ra,
                     112rab, 156vc) as well as one of their children, Ğǝr Wäsän (e.g., 46va, 49vb) are also mentioned in supplication
                     formulas and in Additio 1.
 
 From 2r to
                     35rc the names of the original donors have been erased and mostly replaced with
                     that of Za-Manfas Qǝddus. Za-Manfas Qǝddus is the baptismal name of daǧǧāzmāč Subagadis (1770-1831).</provenance></history>
